-- Netherlands Aims to Double Investment in Nigeria to $21 Billion
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-03-11T19:31:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-11/netherlands-aims-to-double-investment-in-nigeria-to-21-billion.html
The Netherlands is planning to
double its direct investment in  Nigeria  in “the coming years,”
Dutch Vice Minister of Foreign Trade Simon Smits said.  Dutch investments in sub-Saharan  Africa ’s second-largest
economy may increase to 3.3 trillion naira ($21 billion), Smits
said, according to an e-mailed statement today from Nigeria’s
Trade and Investment Ministry.  Amsterdam-based  Heineken NV (HEIN)  owns  Nigerian Breweries Plc (NB) ,
the West African nation’s second-largest listed company by
market value.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Chris Kay in Abuja at 
